text:
🌳🍀🌿A lush green lung leading up a hillock surrounded with private residences.
Peaceful serene area overlooking Sixth Ave.

Peaceful spot at the top of a hill surrounded by terrace houses. No pathways there, so trek at your own risk. Saw a medium sized monitor lizard at the top of the hill. There is a quiet and well maintained playground nearby at the bottom of the hill too.

It's a hill. Enter/exit from:
▪︎The dead ends of Greenleaf Lane or Ming Teck Park (northernmost end)
▪︎Greenleaf View Playground
▪︎Sixth Avenue (keep on left side of drain)
The south and southwestern borders are impassable due to steep slopes, fences, and retaining walls.

Ming Teck Park Green seems to be an unofficial place name so suggested a change of name from the generic "Green" to the more descriptive "hill".
Smashing green space hidden behind swanky housing estate
